<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_1_0.xsd"
      xmlns:p="tapestry:parameter">

	<h1>Conversation Exclusion</h1>
    <p>
    	This page has no conversation handling. If you 
    	<t:pagelink page="NoConversation">open it in a new tab</t:pagelink>, 
    	it will not attempt to reload it.
    </p>
    <p>
    	The conversation handling is turned on by default, this can be configured
    	using the <tt>SymbolConstants.CONVERSATION_ALWAYS_ACTIVE</tt> default.
    	Either way, by using the <tt>Conversation</tt> annotation, this behaviour
    	can be overwritten.
    </p>
    <p>
    	In a regular application, the login-page will likely be excluded from
    	conversation handling.
    </p>

</html>
